    "text": "If you are counting Strait of Hormuz barrels, don’t forget to add the bypass pipelines if you want an apples-to-apples comparison to pre-war levels. \n\nWhat matters is not SoH flows, but Persian Gulf flows. As long as the bypass pipelines continue to be used (and they are), SoH volumes don’t need to return to pre-war levels for overall PG flows to be back to pre-war levels.",
